@ban_cnbl_menu
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ban_support = Q.spd_normalized;

    if (Q.z_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.5;
    }
    if (Q.ddp_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.ddp_normalized * 0.7;
    }
    if (Q.kpd_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.kpd_normalized * 0.6;
    }
    if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.sapd_normalized * 0.5;
    }
    // CNBL is small — banning them only makes sense if they've drifted far right
    // and are actively collaborating with NSDAP
    if (Q.nsdap_r < 20) Q.ban_support -= 0.10; // No real case if Nazis are small

    Q.ban_threshold = 0.55;
    if (Q.pro_republic < 65) Q.ban_threshold = 0.62;
    // CNBL must have drifted toward anti-constitutional collaboration
    Q.can_ban_cnbl = (Q.ban_support >= Q.ban_threshold
                      && Q.cnbl_relation < 25
                      && Q.nsdap_r >= 20) ? 1 : 0;
!}

**Banning the CNBL:**

The Reichs-Landbund is an agrarian nationalist organization whose leadership has increasingly collaborated with anti-republican forces. However, banning an agrarian interest party risks alienating rural voters further.

**Political Support:** [+ ban_support +]
Required: [+ ban_threshold +]

**Coalition positions:**
- SPD: Supporting
[? if z_relation >= 45: - Center: Cautiously supporting (rural Catholic voters complicate this) ?]
[? if z_relation < 45: - Center: Opposed ?]
