@ban_dvfp_menu
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ban_support = Q.spd_normalized;

    if (Q.ddp_relation >= 40) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.ddp_normalized;
    }
    if (Q.z_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.7;
    }
    if (Q.kpd_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.kpd_normalized * 0.7;
    }
    if (Q.dvp_relation >= 45 && !Q.stresemann_dead) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.dvp_normalized * 0.5;
    }
    if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_relation >= 45) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.sapd_normalized * 0.6;
    }
    // DVFP is explicitly völkisch — easier case than DNVP
    // but only if they are still active (dvfp_formed)
    Q.ban_threshold = 0.50;
    if (Q.pro_republic < 65) Q.ban_threshold = 0.57;

    Q.can_ban_dvfp = (Q.dvfp_formed
                      && Q.ban_support >= Q.ban_threshold
                      && Q.dvfp_relation < 20) ? 1 : 0;
!}
view-if: dvfp_formed = 1

**Banning the DVFP:**

The Deutschvölkische Freiheitspartei is an explicitly völkisch and antisemitic party that has collaborated openly with the NSDAP. Their ideology is inherently incompatible with the constitutional order. They are smaller than the NSDAP and the case against them is relatively straightforward.

**Political Support:** [+ ban_support +]
Required: [+ ban_threshold +]

**Coalition positions:**
- SPD: Supporting
[? if ddp_relation >= 40: - [+ ddp_name +]: Supporting ?]
[? if z_relation >= 45: - Center: Supporting ?]
[? if kpd_relation >= 45: - KPD: Supporting ?]
[? if dvp_relation >= 45 and not stresemann_dead: - DVP: Cautiously supporting ?]

**Risks:**
- Moderate — DVFP is small and their voters will flow to DNVP or NSDAP regardless
- Sets useful precedent for banning NSDAP later
[? if nsdap_banned = 0: - NSDAP will absorb most DVFP voters and activists ?]

- @ban_dvfp_confirm: Proceed with banning the DVFP
- @ban_party_menu: Reconsider

@ban_dvfp_confirm
choose-if: can_ban_dvfp = 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if dvfp_relation >= 20: DVFP relations are not hostile enough for a compelling case. ?] [? if ban_support < ban_threshold: Not enough political support. ?] [? if dvfp_formed = 0: DVFP does not exist. ?]
on-arrival: dvfp_banned = 1; constitutional_reform_timer = 18; pro_republic += 2; nationalism -= 3; ddp_relation += 5; z_relation += 3; old_middle_nsdap += old_middle_dvfp * 0.5 if nsdap_banned = 0; old_middle_dnvp += old_middle_dvfp * 0.3; rural_nsdap += rural_dvfp * 0.5 if nsdap_banned = 0; rural_dnvp += rural_dvfp * 0.3; strife += 1; dnvp_relation -= 5;

The DVFP has been banned. Their activists and voters largely flow toward the NSDAP, but the precedent established by this ban strengthens future legal cases against anti-constitutional parties.

[? if nsdap_banned = 0: The NSDAP absorbs most of the DVFP's organizational strength. ?]

- @ban_party_menu: Continue...

@ban_wp_menu
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ban_support = 0;

    // Banning WP requires right-leaning SPD and broad center support
    // WP is a bourgeois interest party, not anti-constitutional — very hard case
    if (Q.reformist_strength >= 55 && Q.wp_relation < 20) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.spd_normalized * 0.6;
    }
    if (Q.z_relation >= 55) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.4;
    }
    if (Q.ddp_relation >= 50) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.ddp_normalized * 0.5;
    }
    if (Q.dvp_relation >= 50) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.dvp_normalized * 0.6; // DVP wants WP voters
    }
    if (Q.kpd_relation >= 50) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.kpd_normalized * 0.5;
    }

    Q.ban_threshold = 0.60; // High threshold — very weak case
    if (Q.pro_republic < 65) Q.ban_threshold = 0.68;

    Q.can_ban_wp = (Q.ban_support >= Q.ban_threshold
                    && Q.wp_relation < 20
                    && Q.capital_strike_progress >= 3) ? 1 : 0;
!}

**Banning the WP:**

The Wirtschaftspartei is a middle-class interest party, not a genuinely anti-constitutional one. Banning them would require demonstrating active collaboration with anti-republican forces, which is only plausible if they have been drawn into capital strike politics.

**Political Support:** [+ ban_support +]
Required: [+ ban_threshold +]

**Conditions required:**
[? if wp_relation >= 20: - Our relations with WP are not hostile enough — no compelling case ?]
[? if capital_strike_progress < 3: - WP must be actively collaborating in capital strike politics ?]
[? if reformist_strength < 55: - Requires a dominant reformist SPD to push this through internally ?]

**Risks:**
- Widely seen as politically motivated — will alarm all bourgeois parties
- DVP, DDP, and Z will all reassess their relationship with us
- Middle-class voters flee to DNVP and NSDAP
- Very weak legal basis — Constitutional Court may reject

- @ban_wp_confirm: Proceed with banning the WP
- @ban_party_menu: Reconsider

@ban_wp_confirm
choose-if: can_ban_wp = 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if wp_relation >= 20: No compelling case against WP. ?] [? if capital_strike_progress < 3: WP has not sufficiently collaborated in anti-constitutional activity. ?] [? if ban_support < ban_threshold: Not enough political support — bourgeois parties will not back this. ?]
on-arrival: wp_banned = 1; constitutional_reform_timer = 24; old_middle_dvp += old_middle_wp * 0.35; old_middle_dnvp += old_middle_wp * 0.25; old_middle_nsdap += old_middle_wp * 0.2 if nsdap_banned = 0; old_middle_other += old_middle_wp * 0.1; new_middle_dvp += new_middle_wp * 0.4; new_middle_nsdap += new_middle_wp * 0.2 if nsdap_banned = 0; ddp_relation -= 10; dvp_relation -= 8; z_relation -= 8; bvp_relation -= 8; pro_republic -= 1; capital_strike_progress += 1; strife += 1; coup_progress += 0.5;

The WP has been banned. The reaction from the bourgeois parties is one of alarm — if we can ban the WP, what stops us from banning them? Capital flight accelerates and our relations with every non-socialist party suffer.

- @ban_party_menu: Continue...

@ban_sapd_menu
on-arrival: {!
    // Banning our own left split — only conceivable in a right-leaning SPD
    Q.ban_support = 0;

    if (Q.reformist_strength >= 65 && Q.sapd_relation < 25) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.spd_normalized * 0.7;
    }
    if (Q.z_relation >= 55) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.z_normalized * 0.5;
    }
    if (Q.dvp_relation >= 50) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.dvp_normalized * 0.4;
    }
    if (Q.srpd_formed && Q.srpd_relation >= 50) {
        Q.ban_support += Q.srpd_normalized * 0.5;
    }
    // KPD will never support banning SAPD
    // DDP very reluctant — free speech concerns

    Q.ban_threshold = 0.58;
    if (Q.pro_republic < 65) Q.ban_threshold = 0.65;

    Q.can_ban_sapd = (Q.sapd_formed
                      && Q.ban_support >= Q.ban_threshold
                      && Q.reformist_strength >= 65
                      && Q.sapd_relation < 25) ? 1 : 0;
!}
view-if: sapd_formed = 1

**Banning the SAPD:**

The Socialist Workers' Party split from us and has drifted toward revolutionary rhetoric. Banning them would require demonstrating that they have crossed into actively anti-constitutional territory — a difficult case, and one that would damage our credibility with the left enormously.

**Political Support:** [+ ban_support +]
Required: [+ ban_threshold +]

**Coalition positions:**
- SPD: [? if reformist_strength >= 65 and sapd_relation < 25: Supporting (reformist wing dominant) ?][? if reformist_strength < 65 or sapd_relation >= 25: Blocking — too much sympathy for SAPD in our ranks ?]
[? if z_relation >= 55: - Center: Supporting ?]
[? if dvp_relation >= 50: - DVP: Supporting ?]
[? if srpd_formed and srpd_relation >= 50: - SRPD: Supporting (they fear SAPD competition) ?]
- KPD: Will never support banning SAPD

**Conditions required:**
[? if reformist_strength < 65: - Reformist wing must dominate our party completely ?]
[? if sapd_relation >= 25: - Our relations with SAPD must be fully hostile ?]
[? if not sapd_formed: - SAPD does not exist ?]

**Risks:**
- Enormous credibility damage on the left
- Workers and left-wing unions furious
- KPD gains from SAPD suppression
- Widely seen as SPD protecting its monopoly on the left

- @ban_sapd_confirm: Proceed with banning the SAPD
- @ban_party_menu: Reconsider

